tellraw @a {"text": "Welcome.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "I see you have spoken to the Last King of Tyre.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "And, you have been... dutifully... reactivating the sacrifices' resonating crystals for him, hm?", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "That's very noble and misguided of you, but it is not why I brought you here.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "I am the Ageless One of Kirion, and this is what you must know.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Reapings are inevitable.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Even if the black crystal had never been worshipped, even if Hoiro had never been founded,", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Yes, even if all humans still lived on the southern continent and never crossed the stormy sea,", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Even then, the reapings would have begun, eventually.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "But, it doesn't have to be this way.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Every man, woman and child has the power to change their own fate.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "All together, everyone can change the fate of humanity.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Many people already know the truth, perhaps you have met some of them yourself.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "What your world needs now, is time.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Time to see the truth.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Saviour Moses sees this, in his own unique way, and in that way he is not so wrong.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Inhumane, cruel, proud and judgemental, to be sure, but he believes the means justify the ends.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Whether you like it or not, you must play the role of divine judge, for you alone have the power to choose.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Indeed, even refusing to choose is a choice in and of itself.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "With that power, you must choose to destroy the resonating crystals.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Ensure no one can ever purge this land.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Condemn the last survivors here to death, for their deaths will save more lives.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "The Circle of Stones is hidden south of the lake, in a valley along the Frontier.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Find the archway along the path.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Pass through it, then circle back around to pass through it again five times.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "Six times in total, forward through the archway.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "The Circle of Stones will appear at the end of the valley.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "There, you can destroy the resonating crystals.", "color": "white", "italic": true}
tellraw @a {"text": "There, you can determine the right end for this all.", "color": "white", "italic": true}